ξ 2. Blaesus, uncle of Seianus, executed after his fall. He was in charge of Pannonia at the time of the death of Augustus (iii 16, 2), when his relaxation of discipline prompted the mutiny of the legions there. Thanks to Seianus' influence he subsequently became ‘ extra sortem ’ proconsul of Africa in 21 A. D.‚ and gained the ‘triumphalia insignia ’‚ and the title of ‘ imperator '.
